# Context — Your Product Facts

*The LLM reads this file when generating content. Only include facts you want in posts.*

## What It Is

- **Name:** [Your product name]
- **URL:** [your-app.com]
- **One-liner:** [What it does in one sentence]
- **Built with:** [Tech stack if relevant — e.g. "Next.js, Supabase, Stripe"]
- **Launched:** [Date]

## What You Can Claim

*Only include verified facts. The LLM will use these in posts.*

- [e.g. "Supports 9 social platforms"]
- [e.g. "Free tier available"]
- [e.g. "API + dashboard + MCP integration"]

## What You Cannot Claim

*Be explicit about what NOT to say. The LLM tends to exaggerate if not constrained.*

- No specific user counts (unless you update this file regularly)
- No revenue numbers
- No "fastest" / "best" / "only" claims unless verifiable
- No roadmap promises

## Audience

- [Who uses your product]
- [What they care about]
- [What pain brings them to you]

## Competitors

*Optional — helps the LLM position your product without naming competitors in posts.*

- [Competitor 1] — [what they do differently]
- [Competitor 2] — [what they do differently]

---

*Update this file when facts change. The LLM reads it every run.*
